This paper proposes a method for improving the representation power and sample efficiency of Gaussian Processes (GPs) using deep probabilistic kernels. The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and probabilistic neural networks, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of kernels, which are also studied in the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SD.
